{"TopicId":211284,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"I had an IDEA","CreatedByName":"adriantheflash","CreatedById":224479,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-02T22:51:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"adriantheflash","CreatedById":224479,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-02T22:51:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I was thinking about it and was wondering if there could be an optional Water requirement for Kerbals\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlike you could collect water and stuff from like the oceans and ice from Duna or other and that I think would add another reason the use ore/maybe ice Tanks for missions and such\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drakenred65","CreatedById":154503,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T03:40:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt all depends on what a Kerbal actually is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif they are desert cactuses the condensation inside the space ship may trigger panic attacks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-01-03T04:06:29Z\u0022 title=\u002201/03/2023 04:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 3, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Drakenred65\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"K^2","CreatedById":57710,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T04:54:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we\u0027re going to have a \u0022life support\u0022 resource, it should be \u0022Snax\u0022. Refineable from basically any rocky body, and work like electricity for cores. If you run out of Snax, your kerbals refuse to perform any ship duties, including piloting, and basically require a rescue. Other than that, they can sulk snaxless indefinitely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WalebKassa","CreatedById":210209,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T06:06:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672721651\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257710\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022K^2\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, K^2 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we\u0027re going to have a \u0022life support\u0022 resource, it should be \u0022Snax\u0022. Refineable from basically any rocky body, and work like electricity for cores. If you run out of Snax, your kerbals refuse to perform any ship duties, including piloting, and basically require a rescue. Other than that, they can sulk snaxless indefinitely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis made me laugh. I really like this idea. It\u0027s a simple solution to the life support system discussion and stays true to the humor of the original game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T06:17:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215174\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672725984\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210209\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WalebKassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, WalebKassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I really like this idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022106975\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3647923838\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149604-minimum-ksp-1122-snacks-friendly-simplified-life-support/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drakenred65","CreatedById":154503,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T06:56:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I was trying to balance the Konsumerism mod I was tinkering with. I realise do that it would have just been easyer to just instal snaks \u002B any life support mod, and getting money was ridiculously easy anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"K^2","CreatedById":57710,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T08:03:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215179\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672726638\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Blaarkies\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Blaarkies said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022106975\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2423671081\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149604-minimum-ksp-1122-snacks-friendly-simplified-life-support/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest indicator that an idea you\u0027ve had is good is that somebody already implemented it.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0Though, I still say it would have been better as \u0022Snax\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-03T17:35:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672721651\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257710\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022K^2\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, K^2 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we\u0027re going to have a \u0022life support\u0022 resource, it should be \u0022Snax\u0022. Refineable from basically any rocky body, and work like electricity for cores. If you run out of Snax, your kerbals refuse to perform any ship duties, including piloting, and basically require a rescue. Other than that, they can sulk snaxless indefinitely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShelter, nutrition, air, clothing, ketchup, sleep\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf anyone else can think of a better K-word, no you can\u0027t. Turns out very few useful words start with K. Maybe kettle (to make tea?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tstein","CreatedById":223854,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-04T10:35:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672767353\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022whatsEJstandfor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, whatsEJstandfor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShelter, nutrition, air, clothing, ketchup, sleep\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf anyone else can think of a better K-word, no you can\u0027t. Turns out very few useful words start with K. Maybe kettle (to make tea?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe tea option is reserved for when you start he career with the British flag as symbol of your space agency.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adriantheflash","CreatedById":224479,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-04T16:16:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYES!!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672828500\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223854\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tstein\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, tstein said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe tea option is reserved for when you start he career with the British flag as symbol of your space agency.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-04T16:25:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224215164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221672721651\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257710\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022K^2\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/2/2023 at 11:54 PM, K^2 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we\u0027re going to have a \u0022life support\u0022 resource, it should be \u0022Snax\u0022. Refineable from basically any rocky body, and work like electricity for cores. If you run out of Snax, your kerbals refuse to perform any ship duties, including piloting, and basically require a rescue. Other than that, they can sulk snaxless indefinitely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think with a bit nuance this is about right. We do know water will be a resource in the game but I think you could just add it to the build cost of new habs and consider it 100% recycled. Same with O2. The important thing is to keep management and mental-math as simple as possible.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-01-04T16:29:00Z\u0022 title=\u002201/04/2023 04:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 4, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Pthigrivi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}